out it lately, probably exactly because<br />it hasn't been very stable under linux)?<br /><br />The floppy and aztcd driver also got updated, and the serial driver should<br />correctly unregister IO ports at module unload time.<br /><br />Finally, the file read-ahead got updated a bit again, and it looks like this is<br />the final version of that code (with possibly tweaks for the amount of<br />read-ahead still to come, rather than changes to actual behaviour).<br /><br />Bring on the penguins,<br /><br />		Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
